These records must be reviewed or audited at least annually, or more frequently as required by the FSRA, to ensure their accuracy, completeness, and compliance with regulatory requirements (FSMR sections 201 and 206). The FSRA has the power to require Authorised Persons to submit reports or information, or to appoint a skilled person to review their AML/CFT systems and controls (FSMR sections 203 and 206). Failure to maintain adequate records or comply with AML/CFT requirements may result in enforcement actions, including the imposition of requirements, variation, suspension, or cancellation of Financial Services Permissions, or the imposition of directions or conditions (FSMR sections 33, 35, 48, 132, and 134).

